OL,6,FThe 47-year-old challenged a June 2023
OL,7,FEmployment Appeal Tribunal judgment,
OL,8,Fwhich ruled in her favour but sent the
OL,9,Fcase back to another employment
OL,10,Ftribunal for a fresh decision over
OL,11,Fwhether her dismissal was lawful - a
OL,12,Fstep lawyers described as
OL,13,F"unnecessary".
OL,15,FIn a judgment on Wednesday, three
OL,16,Fjudges ruled in her favour, finding
OL,17,Fthat the decision to remit the case
OL,18,Fback to an employment tribunal was
OL,19,F"unlawfully discriminatory".
