OL,6,FLord Justice Underhill, sitting with
OL,7,FLord Justice Bean and Lady Justice
OL,8,FFalk, said: "Neither the language of
OL,9,Fthe posts nor the risk of reputational
OL,10,Fdamage were capable of justifying the
OL,11,Fclaimant's dismissal in circumstances
OL,12,Fwhere she had not said anything of the
OL,13,Fkind at work or displayed any
OL,14,Fdiscriminatory attitudes in her
OL,15,Ftreatment of pupils."
OL,17,FSpeaking outside the Royal Courts of
OL,18,FJustice following the judgment, Mrs
OL,19,FHiggs said: "I pray that today will
OL,20,Fprove to be a landmark day for
OL,21,FChristian freedoms and free speech.
