OL,6,F"Christians have the right to express
OL,7,Ftheir beliefs on social media and at
OL,8,Fother non-work-related settings
OL,9,Fwithout fear of being punished by
OL,10,Ftheir employer".
OL,12,FMrs Higgs shared and commented on
OL,13,Fposts which raised concerns about
OL,14,Frelationship education teaching at her
OL,15,Fson's Church of England primary
OL,16,Fschool, rather than at the school she
OL,17,Fworked at.
